    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-03-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 15077/59–60.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Chinese Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 148.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the department’s note of January 21,
                    1909, in which you were advised that the American minister at Santiago had
                    arranged with the Chilean Government for the protection of Chinese subjects in
                    that country, I have the honor to inclose herewith for your information a copy
                    of the certificate<note n="1" xml:id="d73fn1">See inclosure to Mr. Hicks’s
                        dispatch No. 303, January 21, supra.</note> which will be used in this
                    connection and which seems calculated to safeguard the rights of the Chinese
                    subjects concerned. This form is based upon that originally suggested by the
                    department, but which has been amended in certain minor details at the request
                    of the Chilean Government.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
